title: Russian whose daughter drew anti-war picture flees after being sentenced to jail
description: A Russian man sentenced to two years in a penal colony on charges of discrediting the armed forces has fled from house arrest, a court has said.

title: Paris pensions protests are fast becoming a major crisis for Macron
description: The boulevards of central Paris were once again choking up with the fog of tear gas.

title: Olympic chiefs provide pathway for Russians to compete at Paris 2024 games
description: Olympic chiefs today provided a clearer pathway for Russians being allowed to compete at Paris 2024, in defiance of Ukraine, while stalling on a decision.

title: First pictures emerge of Nashville school shooting victims
description: Images of four victims of a shooting at a school in Nashville have been released.

title: Bodycam video shows moment Nashville school attacker was shot dead by police
description: Graphic video has been released of the moment the Nashville school attacker was shot dead by police.

title: Last governor of Hong Kong says 'demeaning and delusional' for UK to soften China criticism over trade fears
description: The last governor of Hong Kong, Lord Patten, has said it is "demeaning and delusional" for the UK to not call out China's behaviour over trade fears.

title: How a US aircraft carrier is part of a high-stakes stand-off in the South China Sea
description: There are few greater displays of US military might than its aircraft carriers - when they move, the world pays attention. They are huge floating cities of sorts.

title: Two women stabbed to death at Ismaili Muslim centre in Lisbon
description: Two women have been stabbed to death at an Ismaili Muslim centre in Lisbon.

title: Plastic surgeon accused of murdering missing lawyer
description: A plastic surgeon in Florida has been charged with murdering a lawyer who was representing his ex-colleagues.

title: Pepsi changes recipe of its classic cola drink
description: Pepsi has slashed the sugar content of its classic drink by more than half.

title: Woolly mammoth meatball - would you eat one?
description:
A meatball has been made from the recreated flesh of the long-extinct woolly mammoth as part of a project to demonstrate the potential of growing flesh 
 from cells.

title: At least 10 dead after fire at migrant facility in northern Mexico near US border
description: Several people have died in a fire at a migrant facility in Mexico's Ciudad Juarez, near to the US border, according to reports.

title: UN calls on Taliban to explain after 'Afghan girls' education activist arrested in Kabul
description: The United Nations has called on the Taliban to explain why an Afghan girls' education activist was reportedly arrested in Kabul.
